{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH8BCRvF1PupNqx1vhGX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. All 3 tests pass, including the new regression test and the two pre-existing ones.\n\n**What was wrong:** `isValidEmail` in `src/validate.js` used the regex `...@[A-Za-z0-9-]+(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$`. The `*` in the middle label group `(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*` let a dot be followed by zero characters, so `..` matched as two empty labels — accepting `user@mail..example.com`.\n\n**The fix:** Changed that single `*` to `+`, requiring every dotted label to have at least one character. Consecutive dots can no longer match, while all valid addresses still do.\n\nThe repro test `rejects consecutive dots in the domain` stays in the suite as the regression guard."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":358,"cache_read_input_tokens":25213,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":358},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dfa80442-9700-4f40-a799-f47ceb4aad62","uuid":"9a4d0bf3-ee63-4cee-aaab-c4faec5ced39","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:50:10.546Z","request_id":"req_011CdH8BBSe2NAia1cPj9aMQ"}
